While working on multi lingual projects (especially in django), we find it hard to switch between locales in minimalist and isolated manner, for example changing locale in environment may cause unexpected issues with other packages, changing using python's setlocale() to constantly change app-level seems unclean and repetitive. 
So we came up with the idea that it would be nice to be able to change that specific strftime() or date instance's locale.

@hvelarde do you have a suggestion on how to make it easier for developers to support AT and DX, Plone 4 and Plone 5?

Regarding supporting AT and DX support in plone.app.event: IIRC, this was the first project which supported both content type frameworks equally. It was a proof of concept and I think the way it's done there is not so bad. If you make use of the awesome feature of behaviors, you'll have to treat attribute access to DX different from AT anyways. plone.app.event shows how (via IEventAccessor) and how to write the same test cases for AT and DX.

