Scanny, unfortunately I didn't have much time to spare this week. However I did look into your mixin proposal. I think this could work for the `Run` and `Paragraph` part, since these both share the `self._element` attribute. If we mixin the object like this:
```python
class BookmarkParent(object):
    def start_bookmark(self, name):
        bookmarkstart = self._element.add_bookmarkStart(name)
        return Bookmark(bookmarkstart)

    def end_bookmark(self, name=None):
        bookmarkend = self._element.add_bookmarkEnd(name)
        return Bookmark(bookmarkend)
```
However, this leads to a problemn in the `_Body` object.  I used the following workaround:

```python
class BookmarkParent(object):
    def start_bookmark(self, name):
        if hasattr(self, '_body'):
            self._element = self._body
        bookmarkstart = self._element.add_bookmarkStart(name)
        return Bookmark(bookmarkstart)

    def end_bookmark(self, name=None):
        if hasattr(self, '_body'):
            self._element = self._body
        bookmarkend = self._element.add_bookmarkEnd(name)
        return Bookmark(bookmarkend)
```
Where the `end_bookmark` method still has to be updated to the implementation where a bookmark object is passed to the `end_bookmark` function

let me know what you think of this solution. 

- Ben

